The rapper appeared in a Los Angeles federal court on Tuesday, Oct. 13, 2015, for the start of a copyright infringement trial in which he and music producer Timbaland are accused of violating the rights of famed Egyptian composer Baligh Hamdi to create their 1999 hit "Big Pimpin'."
